The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation in association with the CAB will organise the first Calcutta Cup a Twenty20 tournament. The league-cum-knockout meet will start from Sunday. All matches, except the final, will be played in three venues Deshbandhu Park, Tala Park and Deshapriya Park. Eden Gardens will host the summit clash on April 28. 

 TEAMS Group A: Calcutta Mayors XI; Chandan Nagar Mayors XI; Asansol Mayors XI; and Bidhan Nagar Chairmans XI. Group B: Siliguri Mayors XI; S. Dumdum Chairmans XI; Howrah Mayors XI; and Durgapur Mayors XI.

 Sagarika Mukherjee beat Ritika Kundu 11-9, 11-9 in the nursery girls category of the Kalyan Jayant Memorial table tennis meet at the Khudiram Anusilan Kendra on Friday. 

 CHESS: State age-group meet at the Bhowanipore Gujarati Education Society from 3 pm.

 TABLE TENNIS: Kalyan Jayant Memorial meet at the Khudiram Anushilan Kendra from 3 pm.




